<subSubSection pageNumber="278" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="278">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="278">Note:</emphasis>
De Wilde-Duyfjes (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="278">Taxon</emphasis>
22: 86. 1973) incorrectly designated a post-1753 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aiströmer">Aistroemer</normalizedToken>
collection (419.3 LINN) as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, and Nordenstam (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="278">Taxon</emphasis>
27: 372. 1978) rejected it in favour of the cited Parkinson plate. However, it seems there may be some disagreement as to its taxonomic identity; Pastor &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Valdés">Valdes</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="278">Revis. Gen.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Penins. Iber." authorityName="Penins. Iber." class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Allium 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="278">Penins. Iber. Islas Baleares</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 141. 1983) question whether it represents 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="278">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triquetrum">A. triquetrum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
